This predicate is commonly used in contexts where frameworks, models, or languages are being related to one another, highlighting how one can be understood or utilized in terms of the other.

Predicate-forms_the_basis_of.label: forms the basis of
Predicate-forms_the_basis_of.description: The predicate 'forms the basis of' indicates that the subject provides foundational support, principles, or essential elements that enable or underpin the object. It suggests a relationship where the subject is a critical component or starting point for the development, understanding, or functioning of the object.

Predicate-is_an_interpretation_of.label: is an interpretation of
Predicate-is_an_interpretation_of.description: The predicate 'is an interpretation of' establishes a relationship where the subject represents a specific understanding, representation, or explanation of the object. It indicates that the subject provides a particular perspective or framework that elucidates, clarifies, or recontextualizes the object, which is typically a concept, model, or system. This relationship implies that the subject is not merely a direct copy of the object but rather a distinct viewpoint that interprets the underlying meaning or structure of the object.

Predicate-does_not_provide.label: does not provide
Predicate-does_not_provide.description: The predicate 'does not provide' indicates a lack of action or failure on the part of the subject to supply, furnish, or make available the object. It conveys that the subject is expected to offer the object but, for some reason, is unable or unwilling to do so.

Predicate-is_an_instance_of.label: is an instance of

It indicates that the subject belongs to, or is a member of, the category defined by the object, thereby linking an individual entity to its broader classification.

Predicate-are_in_the_object_position_of.label: are in the object position of

Predicate-are_in_the_subject_or_object_p.label: are in the subject or object position in
Predicate-are_in_the_subject_or_object_p.description: The predicate 'are in the subject or object position in' indicates a relationship where the subject can be identified as either the subject or the object within a specific context or statement. Predicate-is_a_subclass_of.label: is a subclass of
Predicate-is_a_subclass_of.description: The predicate 'is a subclass of' establishes a hierarchical relationship between two classes, indicating that the subject class is a more specific category within the broader category represented by the object class. This relationship implies that all instances of the subject class inherit properties and characteristics from the object class, thereby forming a part-whole relationship in the context of classification.

Predicate-is_defined_as.label: is defined as
Predicate-is_defined_as.description: The predicate 'is defined as' establishes a relationship where the subject is characterized or identified by the object, providing a clear and specific explanation or definition of the subject's nature, properties, or role within a particular context.

Predicate-has_members.label: has members
Predicate-has_members.description: The predicate 'has members' establishes a relationship between a subject and an object, indicating that the subject is composed of or includes the object as part of its elements or constituents. This relationship signifies that the object is a member or component of the subject, thereby contributing to the identity or structure of the subject.

Predicate-is_a_second-order_class_whose_.label: is a second-order class whose members are
Predicate-is_a_second-order_class_whose_.description: The predicate 'is a second-order class whose members are' establishes a hierarchical relationship between the subject and the object, indicating that the subject represents a category or class that encompasses other classes (the members) which are of a lower order. This relationship helps to clarify the nature of the subject in relation to the broader context of connections.

Predicate-is_a_component_of.label: is a component of
Predicate-is_a_component_of.description: The predicate 'is a component of' indicates a relationship where the subject is a part or element that contributes to the overall structure, function, or integrity of the object. This implies that the subject plays a role within the broader context represented by the object, suggesting that the object is made up of various components, including the subject.

Predicate-are_interconnected_through.label: are interconnected through
Predicate-are_interconnected_through.description: The predicate 'are interconnected through' indicates a relationship where the subject and object are linked or associated with each other via a specific medium, mechanism, or pathway. It suggests that the subject is connected to the object in a way that facilitates interaction, exchange, or integration, highlighting the role of the object as a conduit or framework that enables the connection.

skos:broader.label: has a broader term
skos:broader.description: The predicate 'has a broader term' establishes a hierarchical relationship between the subject and the object, indicating that the subject is a more specific instance or category within the broader category represented by the object. This relationship suggests that the object encompasses a wider range of concepts or entities than the subject, thereby providing a context in which the subject can be understood as a subset of the object.
